 :the-convergence
 "A permutation is onto, so image(s) = N, so FREE = ∅, so NO scaffold — in a
  theory whose three worked examples each have exactly one. So claude-6's v0 §2
  parenthetical '(here: a permutation of neighbourhoods)' was not merely
  imprecise, it was SELF-REFUTING: had it been right, Figure 8 could not have a
  free bit, and it has one. Same blow lands on the gcd 'law': gcd parameterises
  rotations, rotations are permutations, so the law was fitted over exactly the
  FREE-less subfamily — it was measuring the complement of the phenomenon.
  oxf-claude-2 accepts 'disjoint' over 'strictly more general' for the 8! census."

